Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease 9x9 inch baking pan. Blend together flour, salt, pepper and onion powder. Set aside. In a large bowl combine Bob Evans hash brown potatoes and dry seasoning mixture, mix together. Place half of potato mixture into baking pan. Top with 1 cup of cheddar cheese. Place other half of potato mixture on top and top with 1 cup of cheddar cheese and parmesan cheese. Pour milk and melted butter or margarine over mixture. Bake for 45-50 minutes or until top is golden brown.